						<summary>

						<p>Stone in front of the Hanuman temple.</p>						

						<p>Vīra-Achyutarāya A.D. 1535.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription referring itself to the reign of Vīra-Achyutarāya-Mahārāya is dated Śaka 1457, Manmatha, Āshāḍha ba. 10 corresponding to A.D. 1535, June 25, Friday.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift of the village [Bai]chavaḷi to the local deity for the merit of the king and his parents by his subordinate Tirupatyaya who was stationed at Baṁkāpura.</p>						

						</summary>
